# GitHub Linguist language-stats overrides.
#
# This is a Claude Code skills repo: the substance is Markdown (SKILL.md prompt
# design and references). Any code under skills/ and template/ is only an
# illustrative sample/fixture, so it should not drive the language bar.

# Treat everything under the skill and template trees as documentation, so
# embedded sample code (e.g. the C# fixtures) is excluded from the stats.
skills/**    linguist-documentation
template/**  linguist-documentation

# Markdown is the actual content of this repo, so keep it counted. Un-mark it as
# documentation (it lives under the trees above) and force Linguist to detect it
# — Markdown is a "prose" language and is omitted from the language bar by default.
*.md         linguist-documentation=false
*.md         linguist-detectable=true
